# Code of Conduct

## 1. Purpose
We are committed to maintaining a friendly, open, and inclusive collaboration environment for everyone, regardless of age, gender, race, ethnicity, religion, ability, or background.

## 2. Expected Behavior
- Use polite and professional language.
- Respect other people's opinions and ideas.
- Respond to constructive criticism with an open mind.
- Work together to find the best solutions.

## 3. Unacceptable Behavior
- Harassment or discrimination of any kind.
- Hate speech or offensive language.
- Intimidating or threatening other contributors.
- Spamming or irrelevant promotions.

## 4. Enforcement
- Reports of violations can be sent to: roberthamdalah@gmail.com
- All reports will be handled confidentially.
- Violations may result in warnings, contribution restrictions, or removal of access.

## 5. Source
This document is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/) version 2.1.
